headers.header_text: PHY S 100 section 044:  This is a Semester Online class.

catalog.description: Conceptual lectures and demonstrations of the most significant and universal laws and models describing the physical world by faculty from the Physics and Astronomy, Chemistry and Biochemistry, and Geology departments.
catalog.note: NOTE: Satisfies GE Physical Science requirement. NOTE: Additional seats for specific sections may be available to Freshman Mentoring participants through envelopes. NOTE: Help is available for multicultural students. See instructor. NOTE: Also offered by BYU Independent Study; enroll anytime throughout year; one year to complete; additional tuition required; register at is.byu.edu.
